text: Duberildo Jaque Araneda (7 April 1921 – 22 May 2022) was a Chilean lawyer and politician. He was a member of the Radical Party and later the Chilean Social Democracy Party. He was in the Chamber of Deputies from 1961 to 1973. Jaque was born in Carahue, Chile. Jaque died on 22 May 2022 at the age of 101. ==References== Category:1921 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Chilean lawyers Category:Chilean politicians Category:Chilean centenarians Category:People from Araucanía Region
